        <vdl-section heading="Scroll bar">
            <style>
                p.warning {
                    color: orangered;
                }
            </style>
            <vdl-column size="12">
                <p>If you specify a size that is too small for the number of columns to fit in then you can add some CSS to show a horizontal scroll bar.</p>
                <p class="warning">Be aware that this isn't compatible with tables that have pagination controls.</p>
                <code-panel>&lt;style&gt;
    vdl-column.constrain-width {
        overflow-x: auto;
        overflow-y: hidden;
    }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;vdl-section&gt;
    &lt;vdl-column size=&quot;4&quot; class=&quot;constrain-width&quot;&gt;
        &lt;vdlx-datagrid&gt;
            &lt;vdlx-datagrid-column set=&quot;AGENCY&quot;&gt;ID&lt;/vdlx-datagrid-column&gt;
            &lt;vdlx-datagrid-column entity=&quot;AGENCYNAME&quot;&gt;Agency&lt;/vdlx-datagrid-column&gt;
            &lt;vdlx-datagrid-column entity=&quot;NAGENTS&quot;&gt;Num Agents&lt;/vdlx-datagrid-column&gt;
            &lt;vdlx-datagrid-column entity=&quot;MAX_AGENT_ACCOUNTS&quot;&gt;Max Acct.&lt;/vdlx-datagrid-column&gt;
            &lt;vdlx-datagrid-column entity=&quot;MAX_PERC_AGENCY&quot;&gt;Max %&lt;/vdlx-datagrid-column&gt;
            &lt;vdlx-datagrid-column entity=&quot;MIN_AGENT_ACCOUNTS&quot;&gt;Min. Acct.&lt;/vdlx-datagrid-column&gt;
            &lt;vdlx-datagrid-column entity=&quot;MIN_AGENT_COMMISSION&quot;&gt;Minimum Agent Commission&lt;/vdlx-datagrid-column&gt;
        &lt;/vdlx-datagrid&gt;
    &lt;/vdl-column&gt;
&lt;/vdl-section&gt;
                </code-panel>
            </vdl-column>
        </vdl-section>

